               <history>
                 <origin>
                    <origDate xml:lang="ar">غالبا ١٨٩٧-١٩٢٧</origDate>
                    <origDate notBefore="1897" notAfter="1927">Possibly 1897–1927</origDate>.
                   ʾAbbā Qerǝllos, mentioned as <foreign xml:lang="gez">
               አባ፡ ቄርሎስ፡ ዘሀገር፡ አባይ፡ እለ፡ እስክንድርያ፡</foreign> on <locus target="#2r"/>, might be
             <persName ref="PRS3259CyrilV">Patriarch Cyril V </persName> (in tenure <date>1874–1927</date>).
             The identity of Bishop Sǝrābāmon, mentioned on <locus target="#2r"/>
                    (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወዲበ፡ ርእሰ፡ ሀገር፡ አበዊነ፡ ብፁእ፡ ጳጳስ፡ አባ፡ ስራባሞን፡</foreign>)
            is uncertain. He could be Yuḥannā al-ʾAsnāwī, a head of Dayr as-Suryān
            who was consecrated the bishop of the Sudan with the name
            Ṣarābāmūn in 1897. The text also mentions <foreign xml:lang="gez"><roleName type="title"><hi rendition="simple:italic">ʾAbuna</hi></roleName> Lǝqʷās (sic for Luqās?)</foreign>,
         on <locus target="#1v"/>, who is difficult to identify. A later dating to the time of the Coptic
                    <persName ref="PRS3260CyrilVI">patriarch Cyril VI</persName> (in tenure <time><date>1959–1971</date></time>) is less probable.
                    <hi rendition="simple:smallcaps">MSS</hi> <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop20">DS Ethiop. 20</ref>,
          <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop17">DS Ethiop. 17</ref> and
                    <ref type="mss" corresp="DSEthiop24">DS Ethiop. 24</ref>
                    belong together; they are
          probably parts of an unfinished manuscript started in
          <placeName ref="LOC2804Egypt">Egypt</placeName>.</origin>
               </history>

